text: Richard Tomlins may refer to: * Richard Tomlins (politician) (1563–1650), Member of Parliament for Ludlow * Richard Tomlins (merchant) (1564?–1650), founder of the Readership in Anatomy at Oxford * Richard Tomlins (judge) (died after 1660), Baron of the Exchequer 1649–1660
title: Richard Tomlins
